  "prompt": "What is the salary of employee working in media?",
  "response": "The salary of an employee working in the media industry can vary widely depending on several factors, including the specific role, experience, location, company size, and the type of media (e.g., print, digital, broadcast, entertainment). Here are some general salary ranges for common media roles in the United States as of recent data:\n\n1. **Journalist/Reporter**:  \n   - Entry-level: $30,000 - $40,000  \n   - Experienced: $40,000 - $60,000  \n   - Senior/Lead: $60,000 - $90,000  \n\n2. **Editor**:  \n   - Entry-level: $40,000 - $50,000  \n   - Experienced: $50,000 - $70,000  \n   - Senior/Lead: $80,000 - $120,000  \n\n3. **Social Media Manager**:  \n   - Entry-level: $40,000 - $50,000  \n   - Experienced: $50,000 - $70,000  \n   - Senior/Lead: $70,000 - $100,000  \n\n4. **Video Producer/Editor**:  \n   - Entry-level: $40,000 - $50,000  \n   - Experienced: $50,000 - $80,000  \n   - Senior/Lead: $80,000 - $120,000  \n\n5. **Marketing/PR Specialist**:  \n   - Entry-level: $40,000 - $50,000  \n   - Experienced: $50,000 - $70,000  \n   - Senior/Lead: $70,000 - $100,000  \n\n6. **Content Creator (Freelance/Influencer)**:  \n   - Varies significantly based on audience size, brand partnerships, and platform. Can range from $30,000 to $200,000+ annually.  \n\n7. **Broadcast Engineer**:  \n   - Entry-level: $50,000 - $60,000  \n   - Experienced: $70,000 - $90,000  \n   - Senior/Lead: $90,000 - $120,000  \n\n8. **Graphic Designer**:  \n   - Entry-level: $40,000 - $50,000  \n   - Experienced: $50,000 - $70,000  \n   - Senior/Lead: $70,000 - $100,000  \n\nThese figures are approximate and can vary depending on the region (e.g., salaries tend to be higher in major cities like New York or Los Angeles) and the employer (e.g., large media conglomerates vs. small independent outlets). Always check specific job postings or industry reports for the most accurate and up-to-date information.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
